      "title": "[IIP-30] Assets BY delisting, BY yield sources update, Governor update",
      "content": "The IIP-30 considers three proposals already discussed and presented in the [IIP-29](https://gov.idle.finance/t/iip-29-assets-by-delisting-by-yield-sources-update-governor-update/1096). The IIP-29 didn‚Äôt reach the quorum to be executed on-chain.\n\n### Authors\n\nTreasury League and Development League\n\n### Summary\n\nThis proposal focus on three initiatives:\n\n1. Delist RAI, SUSD, TUSD and FEI from the Best Yield strategy and from the IDLE liquidity mining distribution.\n2. Update the yield sources of the Best Yield strategy: remove the Senior Clearpool USDC PYTs and the Senior Clearpool DAI PYTs from the idleUSDC BY and idleDAI BY respectively.\n3. Update the Governor voting delay following the Immenufy bug bounty.\n\n## Rationale\n\n### 1. Delist RAI, SUSD, TUSD and FEI from the BY strategy and from the IDLE LM distribution\n\nFor a comprehensive analysis of the initiative, we suggest visiting the related governance forum posts\n\n* Strategies revamp: unused assets wind down ‚Üí [Forum post ](https://gov.idle.finance/t/strategies-revamp-unused-assets-wind-down/1055)\n* Strategies revamp: unused assets wind down II ‚Üí [Forum post ](https://gov.idle.finance/t/strategies-revamp-unused-assets-wind-down-ii/1090)\n\n> Both BY and PYTs strategies require a good deal of ongoing bandwidth to ensure users have a quality experience. Idle Leagues have been monitoring the performances of the strategies (as reported in the [M2-22 report](https://2235025969-files.gitbook.io/~/files/v0/b/gitbook-x-prod.appspot.com/o/spaces%2F-Lw-v0NTae0RVW1spR9R%2Fuploads%2F2ATYYtmXa6X6sRUxMkqG%2FM2-2022%20Performance%20Report.pdf?alt=media&token=bb721bc4-d4ff-44bb-990c-f1a80510225c)), and due to low profit margins or other externalities (eg [FEI dissolution](https://tribe.fei.money/t/tip-121-proposal-for-the-future-of-the-tribe-dao/4475)) we decided to keep in the main dashboard only the strategies with the most traction and efficiency.\n\n> Following the recent decision of the Aave‚Äôs community (see [Aave‚Äôs AIP-121](https://app.aave.com/governance/proposal/?proposalId=121))\n>\n> [‚Ä¶]\n>\n> We plan to update the assets listed in the Idle Best Yield accordingly, i.e. remove sUSD and RAI.\n>\n>In addition, we plan to delist TUSD tokens. These three assets have never reached a sufficient level of traction to justify the rebalance costs incurred by Idle DAO‚Äôs smart contracts.\n>\n> This initiative aligns with the previous proposal to delist FEI and other PYTs tokens.\n>\n> [‚Ä¶]\n>\n> These four tokens won‚Äôt be anymore listed in the main UI under Best Yield, and deposits will no longer be available.\n\nWe will remove accordingly these tokens from the list of eligible assets receiving the IDLE incentives as part of the Liquidity Mining program distributed to the Best Yield strategies.\n\n### 2. Update the yield sources of the Best Yield strategy\n\nThrough [IIP-26](https://gov.idle.finance/t/iip-26-clearpool-pyts-as-a-new-yield-source-for-by-wintermute/1057/3) and [IIP-27](https://gov.idle.finance/t/iip-27-clearpool-pyts-as-a-new-yield-source-for-by-folkvang/1079/11), Idle DAO approved the Clearpool Senior PYTs as new yield sources, in addition to Aave and Compound, for the BY‚Äôs USDC and DAI markets\n\n> IIP-26 actions:\n>\n> * Add Senior tranche of cpWIN-USDC PYT as a new yield source for idleUSDC Best Yield strategy\n>\n> Together with the above action, IIP-26 will set a new wrapper contract for the Clearpool USDC pool: `0xdb1b149177b5819cf467ad6519cf55416789300a`\n\n> IIP-27 actions:\n>\n> * Add Senior tranche of cpFOL-DAI PYT as a new yield source for idleDAI Best Yield strategy\n>\n> [‚Ä¶]\n>\n> Together with the above action, IIP-27 will set a new wrapper contract for the Clearpool Folkvang DAI pool: `0x67e78ED1cC4732816816A62F2e99CDC5CfaAc06E`\n\nFollowing the FTX collapse, both borrowers, i.e. Wintermute for the USDC market and Folkvang for the DAI one, fully repaid their loans to reduce their market exposure (i.e. utilization rate = 0%).\n\nRemoving these two markets from the Best Yield strategies yield source base will reduce computational complexity and gas costs in managing the allocation, harvesting and movement of funds. These markets could be later added again to the Idle Best Yield if the utilization rate will increase.\n\n### 3. Update the Governor voting delay following the Immenufy bug bounty.\n\nA white hacker discovered a very low vulnerability on a parameter of the [`GovernorBravo` contract](https://etherscan.io/address/0x3D5Fc645320be0A085A32885F078F7121e5E5375) and reported it to [Immunefy](https://immunefi.com/bounty/idlefinance/). We will then update one parameter to increase the Governor voting delay, after a proposal is launched, from 1 to 100 blocks.\n\n## Specifications\n\nThe code for the IIP-29 can be found on GitHub [here](https://github.com/Idle-Finance/idle-proposals/blob/iip-29/scripts/iip-29.ts) and consists of seven actions\n\nIIP-29 actions:\n\n* 4 actions to delist four idleTokens from IDLE BY distribution: RAI, SUSD, TUSD and FEI\n* 1 action to remove cpWIN from idleUSDC BY\n* 1 action to remove cpFOL from idleDAI BY\n* 1 action to increase the Governor voting delay from 1 to 100 blocks (Immunefy bounty)\n\nThe following BY tokens will be removed from the [`IdleController`](https://etherscan.io/address/0x275DA8e61ea8E02d51EDd8d0DC5c0E62b4CDB0BE):\n\n* idleRAI - [`0x5C960a3DCC01BE8a0f49c02A8ceBCAcf5D07fABe`](https://etherscan.io/address/0xf52cdcd458bf455aed77751743180ec4a595fd3f)\n* idlesUSD - [`0xF52CDcD458bf455aeD77751743180eC4A595Fd3F`](https://etherscan.io/address/0xf52cdcd458bf455aed77751743180ec4a595fd3f)\n* idletUSD - [`0xc278041fDD8249FE4c1Aad1193876857EEa3D68c`](https://etherscan.io/address/0xc278041fdd8249fe4c1aad1193876857eea3d68c)\n* idleFEI - [0xb2d5CB72A621493fe83C6885E4A776279be595bC](https://etherscan.io/address/0xb2d5CB72A621493fe83C6885E4A776279be595bC)\n[/quote]\n\n### Next Step\n\nThe temperature checks for the idleTokens removal have already been voted. Consequently, we won‚Äôt open a new temperature check to vote on the GovernorBravo fix and the Clearpool markets removal. The on-chain voting pools will be opened right after the publication of this post.",
